<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-12170] Connect Cast cannot deal with fields of type &quot;bytes&quot; correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-12170</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cast operation on a field of type bytes to a string returns the default ByteBuffer representation, not the content. For example, a field called &quot;payload&quot; of type bytes transformed in this way:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;payload:string&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Returns the result&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;payload&quot;:{&quot;string&quot;:&quot;java.nio.HeapByteBuffer&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;pos=0 lim=4 cap=4&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We propose instead to represent the byte array as a hex string&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;payload&quot;:{&quot;string&quot;:&quot;FFEEDDAABB123F&quot;}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
